            <section ID="s2">
               <id root="21a30dc8-a81c-4dee-bfd5-18d0eb5879e1"/>
               <code code="34089-3" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="DESCRIPTION SECTION"/>
               <title>DESCRIPTION:
</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>3% Sodium Chloride Injection, USP is a sterile, nonpyrogenic, hypertonic solution for fluid and electrolyte replenishment in single dose containers for intravenous administration.  The pH may have been adjusted with hydrochloric acid.  It contains no antimicrobial agents.  Composition, ionic concentration, osmolarity, and pH are shown in <linkHtml href="#t1">Table 1</linkHtml>.
</paragraph>
                  <table ID="t1" width="100%">
                     <caption>Table 1.
</caption>
                     <col width="21.665%" align="left"/>
                     <col width="6.927%" align="left"/>
                     <col width="18.066%" align="left"/>
                     <col width="12.425%" align="left"/>
                     <col width="12.654%" align="left"/>
                     <col width="16.924%" align="left"/>
                     <col width="11.340%" align="left"/>
                     <tfoot>
                        <tr>
                           <td colspan="7" align="left" valign="top">
                              <paragraph styleCode="footnote">*Normal physiological osmolarity range is approximately 280 to 310 mOsmol/L.
</paragraph>
                           </td>
                        </tr>
                     </tfoot>
                     <tbody>
                        <tr>
                           <td rowspan="2" align="left" valign="top" styleCode="Toprule Botrule Lrule Rrule"/>
                           <td rowspan="2" align="center" valign="bottom" styleCode="Toprule Botrule Rrule">
                              <content styleCode="bold">Size (mL)</content>
                           </td>
